The soldiers of World War II knew that every day could be their last. Still, 
they kept fighting and they kept dying. Inside World War II is the intimate 
story of the last global war, told by the survivors. those who endured the 
front line's bloody conflicts. Those who witnessed the brutality of combat give 
their unfiltered accounts. Included in the interviews are former prisoner of war 
and Slaughterhouse-Five. author Kurt Vonnegut and the grandson of legendary 
general George S. Patton.
